## Triplestore stats cache: schema version invalidates stale presentation strings

Context: Even after the previous fixes, the Build page kept showing the old Lakeflow line
(`Lakeflow synced data plane table (UC, separate from graph read path): …bigcustomers_v1`).
The cause was the `dt_existence` cache in `domain.triplestore.stats`: `Domain.save()`
persists it to disk, so the stale formatted string survived both the 5 minute TTL and a
server restart, and kept being served until something explicitly overwrote it.

Changes:

1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py`
   Add `_TS_STATS_CACHE_SCHEMA_VERSION = 2`. `set_ts_cache` writes the version next to
   the timestamp; `get_ts_cache` returns `None` when the persisted version differs, so
   any pre-existing cache (with the old Lakeflow prefix and missing `_sync` suffix) is
   silently dropped on the next read and re-fetched against the current code.
2. `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
   On the load-domain-from-UC path, also pop `_ts_cache_schema_version` alongside the
   existing `_ts_cache_timestamp` cleanup, so the persisted state stays consistent.

Modified files:
- `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py`
- `src/back/objects/domain/Domain.py`
- `changelogs/v0.3.0/2026-05-11.log`

