## DigitalTwin.py: restore from corruption + auto-repair Lakebase union view

Context: Two distinct issues converged on the Build page Lakebase card:

1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py` had been textually corrupted by an
   earlier session — code fragments were spliced inside `_check_snapshot` /
   `_check_registry` and `augment_relationships_from_config` was partly destroyed,
   leaving a `SyntaxError` at line 1604. Earlier `pytest -q` runs only "passed"
   because they hit a stale `__pycache__/DigitalTwin.cpython-311.pyc`. Restored the
   file from `HEAD` and re-applied the intended logical changes cleanly.
2. The "Not loaded" badge stayed on for `managed_synced` graphs even when the data
   was clearly present in Postgres + UC, because `table_exists` only checks the
   readable union view (`bigcustomers_v1`). When a previous Build crashed after
   Lakeflow registered the `_sync` table but before `ensure_synced_union_view` ran,
   the data sits in `_sync` + `__app` but the readable surface is missing.

Changes:

1. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/DigitalTwin.py`
   - Re-apply `_TS_STATS_CACHE_SCHEMA_VERSION = 2` + `get/set_ts_cache` version checks.
   - Re-add `_lakebase_graph_uc_location_display`, `_lakebase_lakeflow_pipeline_uc_display`,
     and a single canonical `_lakebase_graph_target_summary` (the corrupted file had two
     conflicting definitions).
   - In `fetch_digital_twin_existence`, when the Lakebase backend is `managed_synced`
     and the union view is absent, call the new
     `LakebaseFlatStore.repair_synced_view_if_possible` to (re)create the view from
     the existing `_sync` + `__app` sides, then re-probe. `local_lbug_exists` is
     `bool(exists_tbl)` — Loaded as soon as the readable surface is queryable, even
     when the count is still 0.
2. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py`
   - Add `synced_components_status(name)` returning per-object presence (`view`,
     `synced`, `companion`) for the current schema. Uses `information_schema`
     bound to `current_schema()`.
   - Add `repair_synced_view_if_possible(name)`: idempotent
     `CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW` only when `_sync` is materialized; safe under
     concurrent calls. No-op when the store is not in `managed_synced` mode.
3. `tests/test_lakebase_flat_store.py`
   - Cover `synced_components_status` (broken-view state and `app_managed` no-op).
   - Cover `repair_synced_view_if_possible` (repairs when sync present, skips
     when no sync, no-op in `app_managed`).

