## Lakebase schema: Settings → Graph DB is now authoritative (Registry is the fallback)

Context: Operators who explicitly set <em>Settings → Graph DB → Postgres schema</em>
(e.g. `ontobricks_graph`) saw builds materialise tables under the <em>Settings → Registry</em>
Volume schema instead (`ontobricks`). `resolve_lakebase_graph_schema` always returned the
Registry value when set, silently overriding the operator's choice. The schema field looked
"unused" — and the help text under the field actively confirmed that misperception.

Changes:

1. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py`
   Reverse the resolution order in `resolve_lakebase_graph_schema`:
   1. `graph_engine_config.schema` (Settings → Graph DB) when explicitly set wins.
   2. `RegistryCfg.schema` (Settings → Registry Volume) only as a fallback.
   3. `DEFAULT_GRAPH_SCHEMA` last.
   Logs an `INFO` line when the chosen schema differs from Registry so operators can
   see which path was taken.
2. `src/back/core/graphdb/GraphDBFactory.py`
   Stop pre-filling `DEFAULT_GRAPH_SCHEMA` for `cfg.get("schema")` before delegating to
   `resolve_lakebase_graph_schema`. Pass the raw value (including empty string) so the
   resolver can distinguish "operator left it blank" from "operator chose the default".
3. `src/front/templates/settings.html`
   Fix the now-misleading help text under <em>Schema</em> (the field is the operator's
   authoritative choice — Registry only fills in when blank) and under <em>Unity Catalog
   (registration)</em> (UC schema segment now matches the Schema field, not Registry).
4. `tests/test_lakebase_flat_store.py`
   Replace `test_prefers_registry_volume_schema` with the new contract:
   - Explicit Graph DB schema beats Registry Volume schema.
   - Falls back to Registry Volume schema when Graph DB schema is blank.
   - Falls back to `DEFAULT_GRAPH_SCHEMA` when both are blank.
   - Invalid Graph DB schema falls back to Registry.
   - Registry unavailable still returns the explicit Graph DB schema.
5. `tests/test_graphdb_factory.py`
   `test_lakebase_schema_follows_registry_volume_schema` →
   `test_lakebase_schema_honors_explicit_graph_engine_config` (asserts Graph DB wins);
   added `test_lakebase_schema_falls_back_to_registry_when_unset` for the blank case.

