## Build page: Lakebase pipeline status polling + sync-end detection

Context: The Build page never detected the end of a Lakebase managed-synced build
because `trigger_and_wait` blocked a daemon thread for up to 600 s with no task
updates. The frontend had no way to track the Lakeflow pipeline independently, so
if the SDK hung or took a long time the spinner ran forever.

Changes:
1. `src/back/core/task_manager/models.py` — Added `context: Dict[str, Any]` field to `Task`; included in `to_dict()` so the frontend can read it.
2. `src/back/core/task_manager/TaskManager.py` — Added `set_task_context(task_id, data)` to merge runtime metadata into `task.context`.
3. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/SyncedTableManager.py` — Added `get_pipeline_status(name)` non-blocking method; added `on_state_change` callback to `wait_for_completion` and `trigger_and_wait` so the build pipeline can push live pipeline state into the task.
4. `src/back/objects/digitaltwin/_build_pipeline.py` — Before `trigger_and_wait`, stores `lakebase_synced_uc` and `lakebase_pipeline_id` in the task context; registers an `_on_state_change` callback that updates progress message and context with the Lakeflow state on every state transition.
5. `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py` — New endpoint `GET /dtwin/sync/pipeline-status?task_id=…` (or `?synced_uc=…`) that queries `SyncedTableManager.get_pipeline_status()` live and returns `{state, pipeline_id, terminal_ok, terminal_fail, synced_uc}`. Fixed pre-existing Python 3.9 `str | None` type-union syntax at line 2408.
6. `src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js` — `monitorSyncTask` now detects Lakebase context from `task.context.lakebase_synced_uc`; polls `/dtwin/sync/pipeline-status?task_id=…` every 4 task ticks (~6 s); appends live pipeline state to the step description; if the pipeline has been terminal-OK for >30 s but the task is still RUNNING, declares the build complete (30-second grace window for the backend to finish its final lightweight steps). Added `_fetchPipelineStatus` and `_pipelineTerminalOk` helpers.
7. `tests/test_build_pipeline_streaming.py` — Migrated all `patch(string)` targeting class-inside-module paths to `patch.object` to fix Python 3.9 import resolution in mock.
8. `tests/test_digitaltwin_build_log_meta.py` — Same fix: `patch.object(_TSFactory, …)` instead of string-based patch targets.

